licence_overview:
If you intend to abstract water from natural water sources in Scotland, eg coastal waters, watercourses or underground water reserves, you may be required to obtain a licence from the [Scottish Environment Protection Agency (SEPA)](http://www.sepa.org.uk/ "Scottish Environment Protection Agency"){:rel="external"} 

You will only be required to register if your operation is from inland sources of water and between 10 and 50 cubic metres/day or from coastal and transitional waters.

*[SEPA]: Scottish Environment Protection Agency
